"{\"uid\": \"npr.org-2024-08-08-nx-s1-5068065-heres-what-happened-at-the-olympic-track-and-field-events-tonight\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Brian Mann  At the Paris Olympics Thursday evening, the United States has a real possibility of winning several gold medals at track and field events.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 150, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 0, \"end\": 10, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brian_Mann\", \"score\": 0.9999999202057129, \"rank\": 7.979432846739374e-08, \"text\": \"Brian Mann\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q14128148\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brian_Mann\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brian_Mann\"}, {\"begin\": 56, \"end\": 69, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.5685516809114177, \"rank\": 0.755574873991385, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"JUANA SUMMERS, HOST:The man who calls himself the fastest man on Earth, American Noah Lyles, tonight suffered a big upset at the Paris Olympics in the 200-meter final.\", \"from\": 152, \"to\": 319, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 224, \"end\": 232, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9978792939964509, \"rank\": 0.002049653160053153, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 233, \"end\": 243, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Noah Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In front of 80,000 people at the Stade de France, Lyles was trying to pull off the sprint double - a rare Olympic feat - by winning the 100-meter and the 200-meter races.\", \"from\": 320, \"to\": 490, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 370, \"end\": 375, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\", \"score\": 0.9678412931454937, \"rank\": 0.01922336404186936, \"text\": \"Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He was beaten by a runner from Botswana.\", \"from\": 491, \"to\": 531, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 522, \"end\": 530, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\", \"score\": 0.9989043870411272, \"rank\": 0.001024156834136253, \"text\": \"Botswana\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I am here not far from the Stade de France, where I have been watching all of the action on the track with our colleague, Brian Mann.\", \"from\": 532, \"to\": 665, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 654, \"end\": 664, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brian_Mann\", \"score\": 0.9999999202025297, \"rank\": 7.979432846739374e-08, \"text\": \"Brian Mann\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q14128148\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brian_Mann\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brian_Mann\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hi, Brian.BRIAN MANN, BYLINE: Hi Juana.\", \"from\": 666, \"to\": 705, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Wow.\", \"from\": 706, \"to\": 710, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"What a night.SUMMERS: It has been quite a night, indeed.\", \"from\": 711, \"to\": 767, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I mean, Brian, there is been so much anticipation around this race for Noah Lyles, the 100-meter champion.\", \"from\": 768, \"to\": 874, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 839, \"end\": 849, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Noah Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He was going for the double in the 200-meter final.\", \"from\": 875, \"to\": 926, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We saw him bound out when he was introduced.\", \"from\": 927, \"to\": 971, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He was full of that characteristic energy, that showmanship that he is known for, hoping to be the 10th man ever to win both of those races in a single summer games.\", \"from\": 972, \"to\": 1137, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Brian, why do not you pick it up from here?\", \"from\": 1138, \"to\": 1181, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Walk us through what happened.MANN: Yeah, it was clear, Juana, right from the start, that something was different with Noah Lyles.\", \"from\": 1182, \"to\": 1312, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1301, \"end\": 1311, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Noah Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He had that dominant showing Sunday in the 100-meter race.\", \"from\": 1313, \"to\": 1371, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But today, he trailed behind Letsile Tebogo of Botswana and Kenny Bednarek of the U.S. - never seriously challenged them for the lead.\", \"from\": 1372, \"to\": 1506, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1419, \"end\": 1427, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\", \"score\": 0.7644596556454569, \"rank\": 0.3080955781525679, \"text\": \"Botswana\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\"}, {\"begin\": 1432, \"end\": 1446, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenny_Bednarek\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kenny Bednarek\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenny_Bednarek\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenny_Bednarek\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That powerful late kick that he's famous for never came.\", \"from\": 1507, \"to\": 1563, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Then, at the finish line, he collapsed.\", \"from\": 1564, \"to\": 1603, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He stayed on the ground, then rose to one knee, had to call for help.\", \"from\": 1604, \"to\": 1673, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He was later helped off the field.SUMMERS: Yeah, he seemed to be having a really tough time at the end there, and it's not like what we are used to seeing from him, Brian.\", \"from\": 1674, \"to\": 1845, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"What can you tell us about what happened?MANN: Yeah, so Noah Lyles has now confirmed in an interview with NBC that he competed after being diagnosed with COVID.\", \"from\": 1846, \"to\": 2006, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1902, \"end\": 1912, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Noah Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\"}, {\"begin\": 1952, \"end\": 1955, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"score\": 0.9958846236715756, \"rank\": 0.0033001756600749377, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He said, two days ago, he woke up feeling terrible, and he was tested.\", \"from\": 2007, \"to\": 2077, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We also have a statement from U.S. Track and Field, saying they were aware of this test.\", \"from\": 2078, \"to\": 2166, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They knew that he was running sick today.\", \"from\": 2167, \"to\": 2208, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They say that was his choice.\", \"from\": 2209, \"to\": 2238, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"U.S. Track and Field says they did follow all the necessary safety and health protocols.\", \"from\": 2239, \"to\": 2327, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But Noah Lyles was around a lot of these other athletes, so there are going to be some big questions asked about this decision to have him included in this race.\", \"from\": 2328, \"to\": 2489, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2332, \"end\": 2342, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Noah Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Remember, Juana, Noah Lyles has suffered from asthma and allergies in the past.\", \"from\": 2490, \"to\": 2569, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2507, \"end\": 2517, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Noah Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He's talked about that.\", \"from\": 2570, \"to\": 2593, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Despite all this, he still managed to win bronze.SUMMERS: That's right.\", \"from\": 2594, \"to\": 2665, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I am sure we are going to be hearing a lot more about this story.\", \"from\": 2666, \"to\": 2731, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Brian, I do want to ask you to put his performance into context - what he was attempting to do.\", \"from\": 2732, \"to\": 2827, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Just how difficult would it have been and how rare would it have been for Lyles to pull off wins in both the 100-meter, as he did earlier in the week, and the 200-meter, which he attempted to do today?MANN: Yeah, winning these two races in one Olympics is so rare.\", \"from\": 2828, \"to\": 3092, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2902, \"end\": 2907, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\", \"score\": 0.7429102469820642, \"rank\": 0.3189487223817243, \"text\": \"Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Only nine men have done it before.\", \"from\": 3093, \"to\": 3127, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"One of those men, Jamaican Usain Bolt, did it at three straight Olympics.\", \"from\": 3128, \"to\": 3201, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3146, \"end\": 3154, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\", \"score\": 0.9997893695931994, \"rank\": 0.00021066468250144403, \"text\": \"Jamaican\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The last time an American pulled this off was Carl Lewis 40 years ago, in 1984.\", \"from\": 3202, \"to\": 3281, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3219, \"end\": 3227, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9993203869986944, \"rank\": 0.0005547628457239735, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 3248, \"end\": 3258, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Lewis\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Carl Lewis\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Lewis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Lewis\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Lewis was actually here in the stadium tonight watching.\", \"from\": 3282, \"to\": 3338, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But again, along with the rest of us, he saw something very different happen - Noah Lyles coming in with a bronze-medal finish.SUMMERS: Brian, while I have you, I do want to ask you about something else that happened here tonight.\", \"from\": 3339, \"to\": 3569, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Minutes after the 200-meter men's race, Sydney McLaughlin-Levrone won the women's 400-meter hurdle race in dominant fashion.\", \"from\": 3570, \"to\": 3694, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3610, \"end\": 3616, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"score\": 0.9795938813986563, \"rank\": 0.02037598506799662, \"text\": \"Sydney\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was incredible to watch.\", \"from\": 3695, \"to\": 3722, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Tell us what happened.MANN: Yeah, American Sydney McLaughlin-Levrone has been remarkable this year.\", \"from\": 3723, \"to\": 3822, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3757, \"end\": 3765, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9993203869986944, \"rank\": 0.0005547628457239735, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 3766, \"end\": 3772, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"score\": 0.9795938813986563, \"rank\": 0.02037598506799662, \"text\": \"Sydney\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In national trials just a few weeks ago, she set the world record in the 400-meter hurdles.\", \"from\": 3823, \"to\": 3914, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Juana, she actually runs the 400-meter hurdles faster than many professional athletes run 400 meters even without hurdles in their way.\", \"from\": 3915, \"to\": 4050, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She was dominant again, once again broke the world record and took gold for the United States.\", \"from\": 4051, \"to\": 4145, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4131, \"end\": 4144, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9948932072277022, \"rank\": 0.004784721156087104, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A very powerful week - despite the setback for Noah Lyles, we have seen just some incredible performances from American athletes on the track so far.SUMMERS: That's NPRs Brian Mann.\", \"from\": 4146, \"to\": 4327, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4193, \"end\": 4203, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Noah Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\"}, {\"begin\": 4257, \"end\": 4265, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999499484960265, \"rank\": 2.3844154482803344e-05, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 4316, \"end\": 4326, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brian_Mann\", \"score\": 0.9999999995690132, \"rank\": 4.309318565793903e-10, \"text\": \"Brian Mann\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q14128148\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brian_Mann\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brian_Mann\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We are both part of the NPR team that has been here covering the Paris Summer Olympics.\", \"from\": 4328, \"to\": 4415, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4352, \"end\": 4355, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NPR\", \"score\": 0.9999999999078, \"rank\": 9.103194791892068e-11, \"text\": \"NPR\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\", \"Q141683\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NPR\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NPR\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Brian, thank you.MANN: Thank you, Juana.Copyright \\u00a9 2024 NPR.\", \"from\": 4416, \"to\": 4477, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4473, \"end\": 4476, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NPR\", \"score\": 0.9999999999078, \"rank\": 9.103194791892068e-11, \"text\": \"NPR\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\", \"Q141683\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NPR\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NPR\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"All rights reserved.\", \"from\": 4479, \"to\": 4499, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Visit our websiteterms of useandpermissionspages atwww.npr.orgfor further information.Accuracy and availability of NPR transcripts may vary.\", \"from\": 4501, \"to\": 4641, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4616, \"end\": 4619, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NPR\", \"score\": 0.9999999999078, \"rank\": 9.103194791892068e-11, \"text\": \"NPR\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\", \"Q141683\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NPR\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NPR\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Transcript text may be revised to correct errors or match updates to audio.\", \"from\": 4642, \"to\": 4717, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Audio on npr.org may be edited after its original broadcast or publication.\", \"from\": 4718, \"to\": 4793, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The authoritative record of NPR's programming is the audio record.\", \"from\": 4794, \"to\": 4860, \"entities\":