\"from\": 5682, \"to\": 5847, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Brian, why do not you pick it up from here?\", \"from\": 5848, \"to\": 5891, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Walk us through what happened.MANN: Yeah, it was clear, Juana, right from the start, that something was different with Noah Lyles.\", \"from\": 5892, \"to\": 6022, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6011, \"end\": 6021, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Noah Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He had that dominant showing Sunday in the 100-meter race.\", \"from\": 6023, \"to\": 6081, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But today, he trailed behind Letsile Tebogo of Botswana and Kenny Bednarek of the U.S. - never seriously challenged them for the lead.\", \"from\": 6082, \"to\": 6216, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6129, \"end\": 6137, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\", \"score\": 0.7287538257176591, \"rank\": 0.3721991517984913, \"text\": \"Botswana\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\"}, {\"begin\": 6142, \"end\": 6156, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenny_Bednarek\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kenny Bednarek\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenny_Bednarek\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenny_Bednarek\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That powerful late kick that he's famous for never came.\", \"from\": 6217, \"to\": 6273, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Then, at the finish line, he collapsed.\", \"from\": 6274, \"to\": 6313, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He stayed on the ground, then rose to one knee, had to call for help.\", \"from\": 6314, \"to\": 6383, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He was later helped off the field.SUMMERS: Yeah, he seemed to be having a really tough time at the end there, and it's not like what we are used to seeing from him, Brian.\", \"from\": 6384, \"to\": 6555, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"What can you tell us about what happened?MANN: Yeah, so Noah Lyles has now confirmed in an interview with NBC that he competed after being diagnosed with COVID.\", \"from\": 6556, \"to\": 6716, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6612, \"end\": 6622, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Noah Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\"}, {\"begin\": 6662, \"end\": 6665, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"score\": 0.9078619326740459, \"rank\": 0.06883211503968739, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He said, two days ago, he woke up feeling terrible, and he was tested.\", \"from\": 6717, \"to\": 6787, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We also have a statement from U.S. Track and Field, saying they were aware of this test.\", \"from\": 6788, \"to\": 6876, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They knew that he was running sick today.\", \"from\": 6877, \"to\": 6918, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They say that was his choice.\", \"from\": 6919, \"to\": 6948, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"U.S. Track and Field says they did follow all the necessary safety and health protocols.\", \"from\": 6949, \"to\": 7037, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But Noah Lyles was around a lot of these other athletes, so there are going to be some big questions asked about this decision to have him included in this race.\", \"from\": 7038, \"to\": 7199, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7042, \"end\": 7052, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Noah Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Remember, Juana, Noah Lyles has suffered from asthma and allergies in the past.\", \"from\": 7200, \"to\": 7279, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7217, \"end\": 7227, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Noah Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He's talked about that.\", \"from\": 7280, \"to\": 7303, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Despite all this, he still managed to win bronze.SUMMERS: That's right.\", \"from\": 7304, \"to\": 7375, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I am sure we are going to be hearing a lot more about this story.\", \"from\": 7376, \"to\": 7441, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Brian, I do want to ask you to put his performance into context - what he was attempting to do.\", \"from\": 7442, \"to\": 7537, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Just how difficult would it have been and how rare would it have been for Lyles to pull off wins in both the 100-meter, as he did earlier in the week, and the 200-meter, which he attempted to do today?MANN: Yeah, winning these two races in one Olympics is so rare.\", \"from\": 7538, \"to\": 7802, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7612, \"end\": 7617, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trey_Lyles\", \"score\": 0.6312308501772519, \"rank\": 0.46824107797386993, \"text\": \"Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trey_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trey_Lyles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Only nine men have done it before.\", \"from\": 7803, \"to\": 7837, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"One of those men, Jamaican Usain Bolt, did it at three straight Olympics.\", \"from\": 7838, \"to\": 7911, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7856, \"end\": 7864, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\", \"score\": 0.9974757651495467, \"rank\": 0.002530264496161542, \"text\": \"Jamaican\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The last time an American pulled this off was Carl Lewis 40 years ago, in 1984.\", \"from\": 7912, \"to\": 7991, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7929, \"end\": 7937, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9982711537074419, \"rank\": 0.001141775350511899, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 7958, \"end\": 7968, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Lewis\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Carl Lewis\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Lewis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Lewis\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Lewis was actually here in the stadium tonight watching.\", \"from\": 7992, \"to\": 8048, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But again, along with the rest of us, he saw something very different happen - Noah Lyles coming in with a bronze-medal finish.SUMMERS: Brian, while I have you, I do want to ask you about something else that happened here tonight.\", \"from\": 8049, \"to\": 8279, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Minutes after the 200-meter men's race, Sydney McLaughlin-Levrone won the women's 400-meter hurdle race in dominant fashion.\", \"from\": 8280, \"to\": 8404, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8320, \"end\": 8326, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"score\": 0.9289016137013236, \"rank\": 0.07471918608666381, \"text\": \"Sydney\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was incredible to watch.\", \"from\": 8405, \"to\": 8432, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Tell us what happened.MANN: Yeah, American Sydney McLaughlin-Levrone has been remarkable this year.\", \"from\": 8433, \"to\": 8532, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8467, \"end\": 8475, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9982711537074419, \"rank\": 0.001141775350511899, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 8476, \"end\": 8482, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"score\": 0.9289016137013236, \"rank\": 0.07471918608666381, \"text\": \"Sydney\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In national trials just a few weeks ago, she set the world record in the 400-meter hurdles.\", \"from\": 8533, \"to\": 8624, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Juana, she actually runs the 400-meter hurdles faster than many professional athletes run 400 meters even without hurdles in their way.\", \"from\": 8625, \"to\": 8760, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She was dominant again, once again broke the world record and took gold for the United States.\", \"from\": 8761, \"to\": 8855, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8841, \"end\": 8854, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.7324111192119486, \"rank\": 0.33554588099894583, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"