source/Noah_Lyles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He had that dominant showing Sunday in the 100-meter race.\", \"from\": 10713, \"to\": 10771, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But today, he trailed behind Letsile Tebogo of Botswana and Kenny Bednarek of the U.S. - never seriously challenged them for the lead.\", \"from\": 10772, \"to\": 10906, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 10819, \"end\": 10827, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\", \"score\": 0.662835965190022, \"rank\": 0.5086191967033997, \"text\": \"Botswana\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\"}, {\"begin\": 10832, \"end\": 10846, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenny_Bednarek\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kenny Bednarek\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenny_Bednarek\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenny_Bednarek\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That powerful late kick that he's famous for never came.\", \"from\": 10907, \"to\": 10963, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Then, at the finish line, he collapsed.\", \"from\": 10964, \"to\": 11003, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He stayed on the ground, then rose to one knee, had to call for help.\", \"from\": 11004, \"to\": 11073, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He was later helped off the field.SUMMERS: Yeah, he seemed to be having a really tough time at the end there, and it's not like what we are used to seeing from him, Brian.\", \"from\": 11074, \"to\": 11245, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"What can you tell us about what happened?MANN: Yeah, so Noah Lyles has now confirmed in an interview with NBC that he competed after being diagnosed with COVID.\", \"from\": 11246, \"to\": 11406, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 11302, \"end\": 11312, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Noah Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\"}, {\"begin\": 11352, \"end\": 11355, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"score\": 0.9913621358636745, \"rank\": 0.0074189683139098215, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He said, two days ago, he woke up feeling terrible, and he was tested.\", \"from\": 11407, \"to\": 11477, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We also have a statement from U.S. Track and Field, saying they were aware of this test.\", \"from\": 11478, \"to\": 11566, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They knew that he was running sick today.\", \"from\": 11567, \"to\": 11608, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They say that was his choice.\", \"from\": 11609, \"to\": 11638, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"U.S. Track and Field says they did follow all the necessary safety and health protocols.\", \"from\": 11639, \"to\": 11727, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But Noah Lyles was around a lot of these other athletes, so there are going to be some big questions asked about this decision to have him included in this race.\", \"from\": 11728, \"to\": 11889, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 11732, \"end\": 11742, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Noah Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Remember, Juana, Noah Lyles has suffered from asthma and allergies in the past.\", \"from\": 11890, \"to\": 11969, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 11907, \"end\": 11917, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Noah Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He's talked about that.\", \"from\": 11970, \"to\": 11993, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Despite all this, he still managed to win bronze.SUMMERS: That's right.\", \"from\": 11994, \"to\": 12065, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I am sure we are going to be hearing a lot more about this story.\", \"from\": 12066, \"to\": 12131, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Brian, I do want to ask you to put his performance into context - what he was attempting to do.\", \"from\": 12132, \"to\": 12227, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Just how difficult would it have been and how rare would it have been for Lyles to pull off wins in both the 100-meter, as he did earlier in the week, and the 200-meter, which he attempted to do today?MANN: Yeah, winning these two races in one Olympics is so rare.\", \"from\": 12228, \"to\": 12492, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 12302, \"end\": 12307, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\", \"score\": 0.7586166962004737, \"rank\": 0.27417348430960575, \"text\": \"Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Only nine men have done it before.\", \"from\": 12493, \"to\": 12527, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"One of those men, Jamaican Usain Bolt, did it at three straight Olympics.\", \"from\": 12528, \"to\": 12601, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 12546, \"end\": 12554, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\", \"score\": 0.9978299614962246, \"rank\": 0.002170780413938862, \"text\": \"Jamaican\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The last time an American pulled this off was Carl Lewis 40 years ago, in 1984.\", \"from\": 12602, \"to\": 12681, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 12619, \"end\": 12627, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9994416451729736, \"rank\": 0.00044371277837178003, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 12648, \"end\": 12658, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Lewis\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Carl Lewis\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Lewis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Lewis\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Lewis was actually here in the stadium tonight watching.\", \"from\": 12682, \"to\": 12738, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But again, along with the rest of us, he saw something very different happen - Noah Lyles coming in with a bronze-medal finish.SUMMERS: Brian, while I have you, I do want to ask you about something else that happened here tonight.\", \"from\": 12739, \"to\": 12969, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Minutes after the 200-meter men's race, Sydney McLaughlin-Levrone won the women's 400-meter hurdle race in dominant fashion.\", \"from\": 12970, \"to\": 13094, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 13010, \"end\": 13016, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"score\": 0.9925667901216783, \"rank\": 0.007040451843157832, \"text\": \"Sydney\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was incredible to watch.\", \"from\": 13095, \"to\": 13122, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Tell us what happened.MANN: Yeah, American Sydney McLaughlin-Levrone has been remarkable this year.\", \"from\": 13123, \"to\": 13222, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 13157, \"end\": 13165, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9995543430871968, \"rank\": 0.0003875082801241339, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 13166, \"end\": 13172, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"score\": 0.9925667901216783, \"rank\": 0.007040451843157832, \"text\": \"Sydney\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In national trials just a few weeks ago, she set the world record in the 400-meter hurdles.\", \"from\": 13223, \"to\": 13314, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Juana, she actually runs the 400-meter hurdles faster than many professional athletes run 400 meters even without hurdles in their way.\", \"from\": 13315, \"to\": 13450, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She was dominant again, once again broke the world record and took gold for the United States.\", \"from\": 13451, \"to\": 13545, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 13531, \"end\": 13544, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9337636330402237, \"rank\": 0.056698176690902546, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A very powerful week - despite the setback for Noah Lyles, we have seen just some incredible performances from American athletes on the track so far.SUMMERS: That's NPRs Brian Mann.\", \"from\": 13546, \"to\": 13727, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 13593, \"end\": 13603, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Noah Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\"}, {\"begin\": 13657, \"end\": 13665, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9995543430871968, \"rank\": 0.0003875082801241339, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 13716, \"end\": 13726, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brian_Mann\", \"score\": 0.9999999900570629, \"rank\": 9.94251238918079e-09, \"text\": \"Brian Mann\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q14128148\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brian_Mann\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brian_Mann\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We are both part of the NPR team that has been here covering the Paris Summer Olympics.\", \"from\": 13728, \"to\": 13815, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 13752, \"end\": 13755, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NPR\", \"score\": 0.9999960181359862, \"rank\": 3.861914922589643e-06, \"text\": \"NPR\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\", \"Q141683\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NPR\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NPR\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Brian, thank you.MANN: Thank you, Juana.Copyright \\u00a9 2024 NPR.\", \"from\": 13816, \"to\": 13877, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 13873, \"end\": 13876, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NPR\", \"score\": 0.9999960181359862, \"rank\": 3.861914922589643e-06, \"text\": \"NPR\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\", \"Q141683\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NPR\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NPR\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"All rights reserved.\", \"from\": 13879, \"to\": 13899, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Visit our websiteterms of useandpermissionspages atwww.npr.orgfor further information.Accuracy and availability of NPR transcripts may vary.\", \"from\": 13901, \"to\": 14041, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 14016, \"e