Lyles was trying to pull off the sprint double - a rare Olympic feat - by winning the 100-meter and the 200-meter races.\", \"from\": 14410, \"to\": 14580, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 14460, \"end\": 14465, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\", \"score\": 0.996229264719575, \"rank\": 0.0026701741545850414, \"text\": \"Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He was beaten by a runner from Botswana.\", \"from\": 14581, \"to\": 14621, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 14612, \"end\": 14620, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\", \"score\": 0.9993486717904655, \"rank\": 0.0006122008760759048, \"text\": \"Botswana\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I am here not far from the Stade de France, where I have been watching all of the action on the track with our colleague, Brian Mann.\", \"from\": 14622, \"to\": 14755, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 14744, \"end\": 14754, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brian_Mann\", \"score\": 0.9999999900570629, \"rank\": 9.94251238918192e-09, \"text\": \"Brian Mann\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q14128148\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brian_Mann\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brian_Mann\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hi, Brian.BRIAN MANN, BYLINE: Hi Juana.\", \"from\": 14756, \"to\": 14795, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Wow.\", \"from\": 14796, \"to\": 14800, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"What a night.SUMMERS: It has been quite a night, indeed.\", \"from\": 14801, \"to\": 14857, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I mean, Brian, there is been so much anticipation around this race for Noah Lyles, the 100-meter champion.\", \"from\": 14858, \"to\": 14964, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 14929, \"end\": 14939, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Noah Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He was going for the double in the 200-meter final.\", \"from\": 14965, \"to\": 15016, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We saw him bound out when he was introduced.\", \"from\": 15017, \"to\": 15061, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He was full of that characteristic energy, that showmanship that he is known for, hoping to be the 10th man ever to win both of those races in a single summer games.\", \"from\": 15062, \"to\": 15227, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Brian, why do not you pick it up from here?\", \"from\": 15228, \"to\": 15271, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Walk us through what happened.MANN: Yeah, it was clear, Juana, right from the start, that something was different with Noah Lyles.\", \"from\": 15272, \"to\": 15402, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 15391, \"end\": 15401, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Noah Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He had that dominant showing Sunday in the 100-meter race.\", \"from\": 15403, \"to\": 15461, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But today, he trailed behind Letsile Tebogo of Botswana and Kenny Bednarek of the U.S. - never seriously challenged them for the lead.\", \"from\": 15462, \"to\": 15596, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 15509, \"end\": 15517, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\", \"score\": 0.7353539703679867, \"rank\": 0.3598688300088525, \"text\": \"Botswana\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\"}, {\"begin\": 15522, \"end\": 15536, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenny_Bednarek\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kenny Bednarek\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenny_Bednarek\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenny_Bednarek\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That powerful late kick that he's famous for never came.\", \"from\": 15597, \"to\": 15653, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Then, at the finish line, he collapsed.\", \"from\": 15654, \"to\": 15693, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He stayed on the ground, then rose to one knee, had to call for help.\", \"from\": 15694, \"to\": 15763, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He was later helped off the field.SUMMERS: Yeah, he seemed to be having a really tough time at the end there, and it's not like what we are used to seeing from him, Brian.\", \"from\": 15764, \"to\": 15935, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"What can you tell us about what happened?MANN: Yeah, so Noah Lyles has now confirmed in an interview with NBC that he competed after being diagnosed with COVID.\", \"from\": 15936, \"to\": 16096, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 15992, \"end\": 16002, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Noah Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\"}, {\"begin\": 16042, \"end\": 16045, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"score\": 0.9948911032365049, \"rank\": 0.0041817136496714365, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He said, two days ago, he woke up feeling terrible, and he was tested.\", \"from\": 16097, \"to\": 16167, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We also have a statement from U.S. Track and Field, saying they were aware of this test.\", \"from\": 16168, \"to\": 16256, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They knew that he was running sick today.\", \"from\": 16257, \"to\": 16298, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They say that was his choice.\", \"from\": 16299, \"to\": 16328, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"U.S. Track and Field says they did follow all the necessary safety and health protocols.\", \"from\": 16329, \"to\": 16417, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But Noah Lyles was around a lot of these other athletes, so there are going to be some big questions asked about this decision to have him included in this race.\", \"from\": 16418, \"to\": 16579, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 16422, \"end\": 16432, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Noah Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Remember, Juana, Noah Lyles has suffered from asthma and allergies in the past.\", \"from\": 16580, \"to\": 16659, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 16597, \"end\": 16607, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Noah Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He's talked about that.\", \"from\": 16660, \"to\": 16683, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Despite all this, he still managed to win bronze.SUMMERS: That's right.\", \"from\": 16684, \"to\": 16755, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I am sure we are going to be hearing a lot more about this story.\", \"from\": 16756, \"to\": 16821, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Brian, I do want to ask you to put his performance into context - what he was attempting to do.\", \"from\": 16822, \"to\": 16917, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Just how difficult would it have been and how rare would it have been for Lyles to pull off wins in both the 100-meter, as he did earlier in the week, and the 200-meter, which he attempted to do today?MANN: Yeah, winning these two races in one Olympics is so rare.\", \"from\": 16918, \"to\": 17182, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 16992, \"end\": 16997, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\", \"score\": 0.7429102469820642, \"rank\": 0.3189487223817243, \"text\": \"Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Only nine men have done it before.\", \"from\": 17183, \"to\": 17217, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"One of those men, Jamaican Usain Bolt, did it at three straight Olympics.\", \"from\": 17218, \"to\": 17291, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 17236, \"end\": 17244, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\", \"score\": 0.9997893695931994, \"rank\": 0.00021066468250144403, \"text\": \"Jamaican\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The last time an American pulled this off was Carl Lewis 40 years ago, in 1984.\", \"from\": 17292, \"to\": 17371, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 17309, \"end\": 17317, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9993203869986944, \"rank\": 0.0005547628457239735, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 17338, \"end\": 17348, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Lewis\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Carl Lewis\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Lewis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Lewis\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Lewis was actually here in the stadium tonight watching.\", \"from\": 17372, \"to\": 17428, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But again, along with the rest of us, he saw something very different happen - Noah Lyles coming in with a bronze-medal finish.SUMMERS: Brian, while I have you, I do want to ask you about something else that happened here tonight.\", \"from\": 17429, \"to\": 17659, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Minutes after the 200-meter men's race, Sydney McLaughlin-Levrone won the women's 400-meter hurdle race in dominant fashion.\", \"from\": 17660, \"to\": 17784, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 17700, \"end\": 17706, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"score\": 0.9795938813986563, \"rank\": 0.02037598506799662, \"text\": \"Sydney\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was incredible to watch.\", \"from\": 17785, \"to\": 17812, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Tell us what happened.MANN: Yeah, American Sydney McLaughlin-Levrone has been remarkable this year.\", \"from\": 17813, \"to\": 17912, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 17847, \"end\": 17855, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9993203869986944, \"rank\": 0.0005547628457239735, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 17856, \"end\": 17862, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"score\": 0.9795938813986563, \"rank\": 0.02037598506799662, \"text\": \"Sydney\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In national trials just a few weeks ago, she set the world record in the 400-meter hurdles.\", \"from\": 17913, \"to\": 18004, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Juana, she actually runs the 400-meter hurdles faster than many professional athletes run 400 meters even without hurdles in their way.\", \"from\": 18005, \"to\": 18140, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She was dominant again, once again broke the world record and took gold for the United States.\", \"from\": 18141, \"to\": 18235, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 18221, \"end\": 18234, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9998091241376458, \"rank\": 0.0001804511778684808, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A very powerful week - despite the setback for Noah Lyles, we have seen just some incredible performances from American athletes on the track so far.SUMMERS: That's NPRs Brian Mann.\", \"from\": 18236, \"to\": 18417, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 18283, \"end\": 18293, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Noah Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\"}, {\"begin\": 18347, \"end\": 18355, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999501539081046, \"rank\": 3.9810855695342525e-05, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 18406, \"end\": 18416, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brian_Mann\", \"score\": 0.9999999900570629, \"rank\": 9.94251238918192e-09, \"text\": \"Brian Mann\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q14128148\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brian_Mann\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brian_Mann\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We are both part of the NPR team that has been here covering the Paris Summer Olympics.\", \"from\": 18418, \"to\": 18505, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 18442, \"end\": 18445, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NPR\", \"score\": 0.9999999999348574, \"rank\": 6.446390055359023e-11, \"text\": \"NPR\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\", \"Q141683\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NPR\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NPR\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Brian, thank you.MANN: Thank you, Juana.Copyright \\u00a9 2024 NPR.\", \"from\": 18506, \"to\": 18567, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 18563, \"end\": 18566, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NPR\", \"score\": 0.9999999999348574, \"rank\": 6.446390055359023e-11, \"text\": \"NPR\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\", \"Q141683\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NPR\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NPR\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"All rights reserved.\", \"from\": 18569, \"to\": 18589, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Visit our websiteterms of useandpermissionspages atwww.npr.orgfor further information.Accuracy and availability of NPR transcripts may vary.\", \"from\": 18591, \"to\": 18731, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 18706, \"end\": 18709, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NPR\", \"score\": 0.9999999999348574, \"rank\": 6.446390055359023e-11, \"text\": \"NPR\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\", \"Q141683\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NPR\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NPR\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Transcript text may be revised to correct errors or match updates to audio.\", \"from\": 18732, \"to\": 18807, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Audio on npr.org may be edited after its original broadcast or publication.\", \"from\": 18808, \"to\": 18883, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The authoritative record of NPR's programming is the audio record.\", \"from\": 18884, \"to\": 18950, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 18912, \"end\": 18915, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NPR\", \"score\": 0.9999999999348574, \"rank\": 6.446390055359023e-11, \"text\": \"NPR\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\", \"Q141683\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NPR\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NPR\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"BRIAN MANN, BYLINE: Hi Juana.\", \"from\": 18952, \"to\": 18981, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 18952, \"end\": 18962, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brian_Mann\", \"score\": 0.9999999900570629, \"rank\": 9.94251238918192e-09, \"text\": \"BRIAN MANN\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q14128148\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brian_Mann\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brian_Mann\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Wow.\", \"from\": 18982, \"to\": 18986, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"What a night.SUMMERS: It has been quite a night, indeed.\", \"from\": 18987, \"to\": 19043, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I mean, Brian, there is been so much anticipation around this race for Noah Lyles, the 100-meter champion.\", \"from\": 19044, \"to\": 19150, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 19115, \"end\": 19125, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Noah Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He was going for the double in the 200-meter final.\", \"from\": 19151, \"to\": 19202, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We saw him bound out when he was introduced.\", \"from\": 19203, \"to\": 19247, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He was full of that characteristic energy, that showmanship that he is known for, hoping to be the 10th man ever to win both of those races in a single summer games.\", \"from\": 19248, \"to\": 19413, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Brian, why do not you pick it up from here?\", \"from\": 19414, \"to\": 19457, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Walk us through what happened.MANN: Yeah, it was clear, Juana, right from the start, that something was different with Noah Lyles.\", \"from\": 19458, \"to\": 19588, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 19577, \"end\": 19587, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Noah Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He had that dominant showing Sunday in the 100-meter race.\", \"from\": 19589, \"to\": 19647, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But today, he trailed behind Letsile Tebogo of Botswana and Kenny Bednarek of the U.S. - never seriously challenged them for the lead.\", \"from\": 19648, \"to\": 19782, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 19695, \"end\": 19703, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\", \"score\": 0.6398173196786711, \"rank\": 0.5628911863520505, \"text\": \"Botswana\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\"}, {\"begin\": 19708, \"end\": 19722, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenny_Bednarek\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kenny Bednarek\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenny_Bednarek\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenny_Bednarek\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That powerful late kick that he's famous for never came.\", \"from\": 19783, \"to\": 19839, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Then, at the finish line, he collapsed.\", \"from\": 19840, \"to\": 19879, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He stayed on the ground, then rose to one knee, had to call for help.\", \"from\": 19880, \"to\": 19949, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He was later helped off the field.SUMMERS: Yeah, he seemed to be having a really tough time at the end there, and it's not like what we are used to seeing from him, Brian.\", \"from\": 19950, \"to\": 20121, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"What can you tell us about what happened?MANN: Yeah, so Noah Lyles has now confirmed in an interview with NBC that he competed after being diagnosed with COVID.\", \"from\": 20122, \"to\": 20282, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 20178, \"end\": 20188, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Noah Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\"}, {\"begin\": 20228, \"end\": 20231, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"score\": 0.9913621358636745, \"rank\": 0.0074189683139098215, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He said, two days ago, he woke up feeling terrible, and he was tested.\", \"from\": 20283, \"to\": 20353, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We also have a statement from U.S. Track and Field, saying they were aware of this test.\", \"from\": 20354, \"to\": 20442, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They knew that he was running sick today.\", \"from\": 20443, \"to\": 20484, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They say that was his choice.\", \"from\": 20485, \"to\": 20514, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"U.S. Track and Field says they did follow all the necessary safety and health protocols.\", \"from\": 20515, \"to\": 20603, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But Noah Lyles was around a lot of these other athletes, so there are going to be some big questions asked about this decision to have him included in this race.\", \"from\": 20604, \"to\": 20765, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 20608, \"end\": 20618, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Noah Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Remember, Juana, Noah Lyles has suffered from asthma and allergies in the past.\", \"from\": 20766, \"to\": 20845, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 20783, \"end\": 20793, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Noah Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He's talked about that.\", \"from\": 20846, \"to\": 20869, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Despite all this, he still managed to win bronze.SUMMERS: That's right.\", \"from\": 20870, \"to\": 20941, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I am sure we are going to be hearing a lot more about this story.\", \"from\": 20942, \"to\": 21007, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Brian, I do want to ask you to put his performance into context - what he was attempting to do.\", \"from\": 21008, \"to\": 21103, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Just how difficult would it have been and how rare would it have been for Lyles to pull off wins in both the 100-meter, as he did earlier in the week, and the 200-meter, which he attempted to do today?MANN: Yeah, winning these two races in one Olympics is so rare.\", \"from\": 21104, \"to\": 21368, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 21178, \"end\": 21183, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\", \"score\": 0.7586166962004737, \"rank\": 0.27417348430960575, \"text\": \"Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19