aracteristic energy, that showmanship that he is known for, hoping to be the 10th man ever to win both of those races in a single summer games.\", \"from\": 27572, \"to\": 27737, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Brian, why do not you pick it up from here?\", \"from\": 27738, \"to\": 27781, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Walk us through what happened.MANN: Yeah, it was clear, Juana, right from the start, that something was different with Noah Lyles.\", \"from\": 27782, \"to\": 27912, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 27901, \"end\": 27911, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Noah Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He had that dominant showing Sunday in the 100-meter race.\", \"from\": 27913, \"to\": 27971, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But today, he trailed behind Letsile Tebogo of Botswana and Kenny Bednarek of the U.S. - never seriously challenged them for the lead.\", \"from\": 27972, \"to\": 28106, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 28019, \"end\": 28027, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\", \"score\": 0.9548351549039272, \"rank\": 0.04729483528393518, \"text\": \"Botswana\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\"}, {\"begin\": 28032, \"end\": 28046, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenny_Bednarek\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kenny Bednarek\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenny_Bednarek\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenny_Bednarek\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That powerful late kick that he's famous for never came.\", \"from\": 28107, \"to\": 28163, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Then, at the finish line, he collapsed.\", \"from\": 28164, \"to\": 28203, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He stayed on the ground, then rose to one knee, had to call for help.\", \"from\": 28204, \"to\": 28273, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He was later helped off the field.SUMMERS: Yeah, he seemed to be having a really tough time at the end there, and it's not like what we are used to seeing from him, Brian.\", \"from\": 28274, \"to\": 28445, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"What can you tell us about what happened?MANN: Yeah, so Noah Lyles has now confirmed in an interview with NBC that he competed after being diagnosed with COVID.\", \"from\": 28446, \"to\": 28606, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 28502, \"end\": 28512, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Noah Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\"}, {\"begin\": 28552, \"end\": 28555, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"score\": 0.981526421548914, \"rank\": 0.016012812722888473, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He said, two days ago, he woke up feeling terrible, and he was tested.\", \"from\": 28607, \"to\": 28677, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We also have a statement from U.S. Track and Field, saying they were aware of this test.\", \"from\": 28678, \"to\": 28766, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They knew that he was running sick today.\", \"from\": 28767, \"to\": 28808, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They say that was his choice.\", \"from\": 28809, \"to\": 28838, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"U.S. Track and Field says they did follow all the necessary safety and health protocols.\", \"from\": 28839, \"to\": 28927, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But Noah Lyles was around a lot of these other athletes, so there are going to be some big questions asked about this decision to have him included in this race.\", \"from\": 28928, \"to\": 29089, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 28932, \"end\": 28942, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Noah Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Remember, Juana, Noah Lyles has suffered from asthma and allergies in the past.\", \"from\": 29090, \"to\": 29169, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 29107, \"end\": 29117, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Noah Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He's talked about that.\", \"from\": 29170, \"to\": 29193, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Despite all this, he still managed to win bronze.SUMMERS: That's right.\", \"from\": 29194, \"to\": 29265, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I am sure we are going to be hearing a lot more about this story.\", \"from\": 29266, \"to\": 29331, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Brian, I do want to ask you to put his performance into context - what he was attempting to do.\", \"from\": 29332, \"to\": 29427, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Just how difficult would it have been and how rare would it have been for Lyles to pull off wins in both the 100-meter, as he did earlier in the week, and the 200-meter, which he attempted to do today?MANN: Yeah, winning these two races in one Olympics is so rare.\", \"from\": 29428, \"to\": 29692, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 29502, \"end\": 29507, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trey_Lyles\", \"score\": 0.5665125515503097, \"rank\": 0.7329260174760622, \"text\": \"Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trey_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trey_Lyles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Only nine men have done it before.\", \"from\": 29693, \"to\": 29727, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"One of those men, Jamaican Usain Bolt, did it at three straight Olympics.\", \"from\": 29728, \"to\": 29801, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 29746, \"end\": 29754, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\", \"score\": 0.9937051038437701, \"rank\": 0.00633146901597152, \"text\": \"Jamaican\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The last time an American pulled this off was Carl Lewis 40 years ago, in 1984.\", \"from\": 29802, \"to\": 29881, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 29819, \"end\": 29827, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9994380751338291, \"rank\": 0.00042052759097618457, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 29848, \"end\": 29858, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Lewis\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Carl Lewis\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Lewis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Lewis\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Lewis was actually here in the stadium tonight watching.\", \"from\": 29882, \"to\": 29938, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But again, along with the rest of us, he saw something very different happen - Noah Lyles coming in with a bronze-medal finish.SUMMERS: Brian, while I have you, I do want to ask you about something else that happened here tonight.\", \"from\": 29939, \"to\": 30169, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Minutes after the 200-meter men's race, Sydney McLaughlin-Levrone won the women's 400-meter hurdle race in dominant fashion.\", \"from\": 30170, \"to\": 30294, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 30210, \"end\": 30216, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"score\": 0.9925667901216783, \"rank\": 0.007040451843157832, \"text\": \"Sydney\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was incredible to watch.\", \"from\": 30295, \"to\": 30322, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Tell us what happened.MANN: Yeah, American Sydney McLaughlin-Levrone has been remarkable this year.\", \"from\": 30323, \"to\": 30422, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 30357, \"end\": 30365, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9995543430871968, \"rank\": 0.0003875082801241339, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 30366, \"end\": 30372, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"score\": 0.9925667901216783, \"rank\": 0.007040451843157832, \"text\": \"Sydney\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In national trials just a few weeks ago, she set the world record in the 400-meter hurdles.\", \"from\": 30423, \"to\": 30514, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Juana, she actually runs the 400-meter hurdles faster than many professional athletes run 400 meters even without hurdles in their way.\", \"from\": 30515, \"to\": 30650, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She was dominant again, once again broke the world record and took gold for the United States.\", \"from\": 30651, \"to\": 30745, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 30731, \"end\": 30744, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/res