ia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He said, two days ago, he woke up feeling terrible, and he was tested.\", \"from\": 32745, \"to\": 32815, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We also have a statement from U.S. Track and Field, saying they were aware of this test.\", \"from\": 32816, \"to\": 32904, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They knew that he was running sick today.\", \"from\": 32905, \"to\": 32946, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They say that was his choice.\", \"from\": 32947, \"to\": 32976, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"U.S. Track and Field says they did follow all the necessary safety and health protocols.\", \"from\": 32977, \"to\": 33065, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But Noah Lyles was around a lot of these other athletes, so there are going to be some big questions asked about this decision to have him included in this race.\", \"from\": 33066, \"to\": 33227, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 33070, \"end\": 33080, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Noah Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Remember, Juana, Noah Lyles has suffered from asthma and allergies in the past.\", \"from\": 33228, \"to\": 33307, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 33245, \"end\": 33255, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Noah Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He's talked about that.\", \"from\": 33308, \"to\": 33331, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Despite all this, he still managed to win bronze.SUMMERS: That's right.\", \"from\": 33332, \"to\": 33403, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I am sure we are going to be hearing a lot more about this story.\", \"from\": 33404, \"to\": 33469, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Brian, I do want to ask you to put his performance into context - what he was attempting to do.\", \"from\": 33470, \"to\": 33565, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Just how difficult would it have been and how rare would it have been for Lyles to pull off wins in both the 100-meter, as he did earlier in the week, and the 200-meter, which he attempted to do today?MANN: Yeah, winning these two races in one Olympics is so rare.\", \"from\": 33566, \"to\": 33830, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 33640, \"end\": 33645, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trey_Lyles\", \"score\": 0.5665125515503097, \"rank\": 0.7329260174760622, \"text\": \"Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trey_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trey_Lyles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Only nine men have done it before.\", \"from\": 33831, \"to\": 33865, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"One of those men, Jamaican Usain Bolt, did it at three straight Olympics.\", \"from\": 33866, \"to\": 33939, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 33884, \"end\": 33892, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\", \"score\": 0.9937051038437701, \"rank\": 0.00633146901597152, \"text\": \"Jamaican\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The last time an American pulled this off was Carl Lewis 40 years ago, in 1984.\", \"from\": 33940, \"to\": 34019, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 33957, \"end\": 33965, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9994380751338291, \"rank\": 0.00042052759097618457, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 33986, \"end\": 33996, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Lewis\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Carl Lewis\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Lewis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Lewis\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Lewis was actually here in the stadium tonight watching.\", \"from\": 34020, \"to\": 34076, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But again, along with the rest of us, he saw something very different happen - Noah Lyles coming in with a bronze-medal finish.SUMMERS: Brian, while I have you, I do want to ask you about something else that happened here tonight.\", \"from\": 34077, \"to\": 34307, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Minutes after the 200-meter men's race, Sydney McLaughlin-Levrone won the women's 400-meter hurdle race in dominant fashion.\", \"from\": 34308, \"to\": 34432, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 34348, \"end\": 34354, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"score\": 0.9925667901216783, \"rank\": 0.007040451843157832, \"text\": \"Sydney\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was incredible to watch.\", \"from\": 34433, \"to\": 34460, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Tell us what happened.MANN: Yeah, American Sydney McLaughlin-Levrone has been remarkable this year.\", \"from\": 34461, \"to\": 34560, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 34495, \"end\": 34503, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9995543430871968, \"rank\": 0.0003875082801241339, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 34504, \"end\": 34510, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"score\": 0.9925667901216783, \"rank\": 0.007040451843157832, \"text\": \"Sydney\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In national trials just a few weeks ago, she set the world record in the 400-meter hurdles.\", \"from\": 34561, \"to\": 34652, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Juana, she actually runs the 400-meter hurdles faster than many professional athletes run 400 meters even without hurdles in their way.\", \"from\": 34653, \"to\": 34788, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She was dominant again, once again broke the world record and took gold for the United States.\", \"from\": 34789, \"to\": 34883, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 34869, \"end\": 34882, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9337636330402237, \"rank\": 0.056698176690902546, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A very powerful week - despite the setback for Noah Lyles, we have seen just some incredible performances from American athletes on the track so far.SUMMERS: That's NPRs Brian Mann.\", \"from\": 34884, \"to\": 35065, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 34931, \"end\": 34941, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Noah Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\"}, {\"begin\": 34995, \"end\": 35003, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9995543430871968, \"rank\": 0.0003875082801241339, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 35054, \"end\": 35064, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brian_Mann\", \"score\": 0.9999999900570629, \"rank\": 9.94251238918079e-09, \"text\": \"Brian Mann\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q14128148\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brian_Mann\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brian_Mann\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We are both part of the NPR team that has been here covering the Paris Summer Olympics.\", \"from\": 35066, \"to\": 35153, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 35090, \"end\": 35093, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NPR\", \"score\": 0.9999960181359862, \"rank\": 3.861914922589643e-06, \"text\": \"NPR\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\", \"Q141683\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NPR\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NPR\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Brian, thank you.MANN: Thank you, Juana.Copyright \\u00a9 2024 NPR.\", \"from\": 35154, \"to\": 35215, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 35211, \"end\": 35214, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NPR\", \"score\": 0.9999960181359862, \"rank\": 3.861914922589643e-06, \"text\": \"NPR\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\", \"Q141683\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NPR\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NPR\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"All rights reserved.\", \"from\": 35217, \"to\": 35237, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Visit our websiteterms of useandpermissionspages atwww.npr.orgfor further information.Accuracy and availability of NPR transcripts may vary.\", \"from\": 35239, \"to\": 35379, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 35354, \"end\": 35357, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NPR\", \"score\": 0.9999960181359862, \"rank\": 3.861914922589643e-06, \"text\": \"NPR\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\", \"Q141683\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NPR\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NPR\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Transcript text may be revised to correct errors or match updates to audio.\", \"from\": 35380, \"to\": 35455, \"enti