 way.\", \"from\": 38303, \"to\": 38438, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She was dominant again, once again broke the world record and took gold for the United States.\", \"from\": 38439, \"to\": 38533, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 38519, \"end\": 38532, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9998654297459147, \"rank\": 0.0001285081719423714, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A very powerful week - despite the setback for Noah Lyles, we have seen just some incredible performances from American athletes on the track so far.SUMMERS: That's NPRs Brian Mann.\", \"from\": 38534, \"to\": 38715, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 38581, \"end\": 38591, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Noah Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\"}, {\"begin\": 38645, \"end\": 38653, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999263395150578, \"rank\": 4.9519265289894034e-05, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 38704, \"end\": 38714, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brian_Mann\", \"score\": 0.9999999900570629, \"rank\": 9.94251238918192e-09, \"text\": \"Brian Mann\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q14128148\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brian_Mann\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brian_Mann\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We are both part of the NPR team that has been here covering the Paris Summer Olympics.\", \"from\": 38716, \"to\": 38803, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 38740, \"end\": 38743, \"