as attempting to do.\", \"from\": 50053, \"to\": 50148, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Just how difficult would it have been and how rare would it have been for Lyles to pull off wins in both the 100-meter, as he did earlier in the week, and the 200-meter, which he attempted to do today?MANN: Yeah, winning these two races in one Olympics is so rare.\", \"from\": 50149, \"to\": 50413, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 50223, \"end\": 50228, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\", \"score\": 0.7336950964412635, \"rank\": 0.31894872238168803, \"text\": \"Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Only nine men have done it before.\", \"from\": 50414, \"to\": 50448, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"One of those men, Jamaican Usain Bolt, did it at three straight Olympics.\", \"from\": 50449, \"to\": 50522, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 50467, \"end\": 50475, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\", \"score\": 0.9995262990346285, \"rank\": 0.00047388715892194015, \"text\": \"Jamaican\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The last time an American pulled this off was Carl Lewis 40 years ago, in 1984.\", \"from\": 50523, \"to\": 50602, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 50540, \"end\": 50548, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9993329854385699, \"rank\": 0.0005726027589065963, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 50569, \"end\": 50579, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Lewis\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Carl Lewis\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Lewis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Lewis\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Lewis was actually here in the stadium tonight watching.\", \"from\": 50603, \"to\": 50659, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But again, along with the rest of us, he saw something very different happen - Noah Lyles coming in with a bronze-medal finish.SUMMERS: Brian, while I have you, I do want to ask you about something else that happened here tonight.\", \"from\": 50660, \"to\": 50890, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Minutes after the 200-meter men's race, Sydney McLaughlin-Levrone won the women's 400-meter hurdle race in dominant fashion.\", \"from\": 50891, \"to\": 51015, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 50931, \"end\": 50937, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"score\": 0.9799211554470496, \"rank\": 0.01997063031320917, \"text\": \"Sydney\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was incredible to watch.\", \"from\": 51016, \"to\": 51043, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Tell us what happened.MANN: Yeah, American Sydney McLaughlin-Levrone has been remarkable this year.\", \"from\": 51044, \"to\": 51143, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 51078, \"end\": 51086, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999624261676315, \"rank\": 1.8339996835089454e-05, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 51087, \"end\": 51093, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"score\": 0.9941619748403525, \"rank\": 0.005442885703679754, \"text\": \"Sydney\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In national trials just a few weeks ago, she set the world record in the 400-meter hurdles.\", \"from\": 51144, \"to\": 51235, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Juana, she actually runs the 400-meter hurdles faster than many professional athletes run 400 meters even without hurdles in their way.\", \"from\": 51236, \"to\": 51371, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She was dominant again, once again broke the world record and took gold for the United States.\", \"from\": 51372, \"to\": 51466, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 51452, \"end\": 51465, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9996441731807163, \"rank\": 0.00033253310076712184, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A very powerful week - despite the setback for Noah Lyles, we have seen just some incredible performances from American athletes on the track so far.SUMMERS: That's NPRs Brian Mann.\", \"from\": 51467, \"to\": 51648, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 51514, \"end\": 51524, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Noah Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\"}, {\"begin\": 51578, \"end\": 51586, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999624261676315, \"rank\": 1.8339996835089454e-05, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 51637, \"end\": 51647, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brian_Mann\", \"score\": 0.9999999900570629, \"rank\": 9.94251238918079e-09, \"text\": \"Brian Mann\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q14128148\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/